summary: SummaryHighlightsVeganGive BackMaybelline's Fit Me Concealer conceals redness, flaws, and blemishes to achieve a more flawless skin complexion. This natural finish concealer is breathable, oil-free, and won't clog pores.
details: DetailsBenefitsProvides natural looking coverage that instantly eliminates dark circles & imperfectionsMatches skin tones to deliver a more even complexion with lasting wearFeaturesFragrance freeNon-comedogenicDermatologist testedAllergy-testedOphthalmologist tested & suitable for sensitive skinItem 2225219How To UseStep 1. Dot the liquid concealer onto imperfections or under the eyes to conceal the look of dark circles.Step 2. Pat the concealer with a finger or brush to blend.IngredientsDeep: Water (Aqua), Cyclopentasiloxane, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Glycerin, Sorbitan Isostearate, Propylene Glycol, Titanium Dioxide, Ozokerite, Phenoxyethanol, Magnesium Sulfate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Methylparaben, Acrylates Crosspolymer, Alumina, Butylparaben, Aluminum Hydroxide, Tocopherol, Silica, Chamomilla Recutita (Matricaria Flower Extract). reviews.headline: A new staple
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I love this concealer. It looks great under my eyes. It's not cakey and doesn't crease on me. It's easy to blend and stays put all day long. It's a new staple in my makeup routine!

reviews.headline: Would definitely buy again
reviews.comments: I just barely started using it but I worked really good at covering. I have ance and it worked good at covering the redness but you could see the texture of it which is normal. I would definitely recommend but some shades are a bit orange so watch out.

reviews.headline: LOVE
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I have sensitive acne prone oily but dehydrated skin and this doesn't break me out or separate on my face! It lays well on texture and a little goes a long way.

reviews.headline: Would buy this again
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The packaging is great and the bledability is great and the coverage is awesome and the texture is perfect and I love the shade range of it was great.

reviews.headline: Love this concealer!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I like this concealer for many years. I love how it looks natural and light but so hydrating in the same time. It is easy to apply and has many shades.

reviews.headline: Silky skin
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This product was very nice to apply. It went on great covered up all my blemishes and made my skin look flawless turned out beautifully perfect shade match and love everything about this.

reviews.headline: I will buy this forever
reviews.comments: It is a perfect affordable concealer and a great dupe for the nars concealer

reviews.headline: Blends nicely
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] It's a light creamy texture. Doesn't feel heavy on my skin and blends very nicely. The packaging is nice and I'm very happy with the applicator. Really brightened up my under eyes.

reviews.headline: NARS dupe
reviews.comments: I've used this concealer before and it definitely lives up to its viral hype. It's a nars dupe. Goes on medium coverage. Blends nice. I use a light shade for underneath my eyes and a dark shade for contouring.

reviews.headline: I would buy again
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I have used this brand for concealer before and I enjoyed it. This time I used it for contour and got shades darker than my skin and it worked good. It blended super well and not dried up in seconds.

reviews.headline: Really good concealer
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review]. I really like this concealer. It is easy to use with a lip gloss style packaging. There are no harsh smells and blends easy with my skin. The coverage could be a little thicker but over all is a good shade and is workable.

reviews.headline: I would buy this again and again
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This concealer is one of my absolute favorites at the drugstore. Time after time it provides me with creaseless, brightened under eyes that could not look more flawless. For an extra pale girl like me the lightest shades are perfect!

reviews.headline: I will definitely be buying
reviews.comments: I received this product in exchange for my honest review and I absolutely fell in love with it. Very inexpensive and covered my dark circles without creating more fine lines with my aging skin.

reviews.headline: been buying this concealer for years!
reviews.comments: I love it so much and it's AFFORDABLE!!

reviews.headline: Decent
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Blends nicely, medium ish coverage, okay shade range. The bottle is very small, I was not expecting it to be that small for the price I paid but otherwise it's a good product

reviews.headline: I would buy again
reviews.comments: I got the wrong shade but I have used this before. I like how lightweight it is so I use it when I'm not feeling like a full face type of day !

reviews.headline: Maybelline Fit Me Concealer
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The Maybelline Fit Me Concealer has a medium coverage. I like the applicator. The light color worked great for under eyes to brighten. It is long lasting

reviews.headline: RIDE OR DIE
reviews.comments: Second concealer i ever used, tarte being my first. I have over 10 concealer brands in my makeup drawer but i always come back to use this one. something magical is in it. It does not crease at all, it doesnt pill and its not drying!! coming from someone with the dryest skin on earth. Conceals acne perfectly especially if you use a dot of green color corrector beforehand, also coming from someone who struggles with awful hormonal acne. Ive had the same bottle for two years, disgusting? Idc. My point is it doesnt go bad and it lasts forever. I cant believe theres even bad reviews. I literally have nothing bad to say

reviews.headline: Perfect for  spot conceal
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The concealer is the perfect shade for my "no make up" days. I use to spot conceal and simply add blush and my face is complete! It's super creamy and not drying at all and lasts all day.

reviews.headline: Owow
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I've used this for 10 years. It's not too heavy but good to clear blemishes. Very blendable and very good texture. I buy in various shades so I can contour

faceoff_positive.comments: I really like this. I have the liquid foundation, foundation stick, and powder foundation and I really like it. It has light to medium coverage and I prefer full coverage, so I have to use a concealer on my acne scars. I would use the fit me concealer, because it's an amazing formula except that the LIGHTEST shade is DARKER than the lightest foundation shade. what??? I would give this five stars if I could actually use the concealer, because I love the coverage and wear, but the color is way too dark. What brand would make their lightest concealer darker than their lightest foundation shade??? I want to see an almost white concealer, Maybelline. Us pale folks want to highlight our undereyes too.
faceoff_positive.headline: Great, but not full coverage or shade selection

faceoff_negative.comments: I love this concealer. It stays all day and looks amazing, but they changed the numbering system. My old number was 15 fair. I went to the store today to buy some more because I was running out. I made sure I got 15 because I remember that light was darker than fair and it was shade 10. Now shade 15 is light and the tube says the old numbering system of 10. It's more than a little frustrating because now I have to return the concealer and get my right shade all because they switched the numbering system.
faceoff_negative.headline: Love, but...
